# HTML Development Rules

## [STRICT] HTML Structure Requirements

### 1. Document Type and Meta Tags
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Page description for SEO">
    <title>Page Title</title>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Content goes here -->
</body>
</html>
```

### 2. Semantic HTML Elements
- **ALWAYS** use semantic elements: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`
- **NEVER** use `<div>` for semantic purposes
- **ALWAYS** use proper heading hierarchy: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`

### 3. Accessibility Requirements
- **ALWAYS** include `alt` attributes for images
- **ALWAYS** use `aria-label` for interactive elements
- **ALWAYS** ensure proper focus management
- **ALWAYS** use proper form labels

### 4. Form Structure
```html
<form action="/submit" method="POST" novalidate>
    <fieldset>
        <legend>Form Title</legend>
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email">Email Address</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required aria-describedby="email-help">
            <small id="email-help">Enter your email address</small>
        </div>
    </fieldset>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

### 5. Image Optimization
```html
<img src="image.jpg" 
     alt="Descriptive alt text" 
     width="300" 
     height="200" 
     loading="lazy"
     srcset="image-300w.jpg 300w, image-600w.jpg 600w"
     sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300px, 600px">
```

### 6. Table Structure
```html
<table>
    <caption>Table Description</caption>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th scope="col">Column 1</th>
            <th scope="col">Column 2</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Data 1</td>
            <td>Data 2</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
```

## [GUIDELINE] Best Practices

### Code Organization
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Group related elements together
- Add comments for complex sections
- Use meaningful class and ID names

### Performance
- Minimize DOM depth
- Use efficient selectors
- Optimize images
- Use lazy loading for images

### SEO
- Use proper heading hierarchy
- Include meta descriptions
- Use semantic markup
- Optimize for mobile

## [STRICT] Validation Rules

### HTML Validation
- **ALWAYS** validate HTML with W3C validator
- **ALWAYS** ensure proper nesting
- **ALWAYS** close all tags
- **ALWAYS** use lowercase for attributes

### Accessibility Validation
- **ALWAYS** test with screen readers
- **ALWAYS** ensure keyboard navigation
- **ALWAYS** check color contrast
- **ALWAYS** validate ARIA attributes

